The paper deals with the problem of collective entity disambiguation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new objective function and an iterative solution for the problem, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of knowledge bases, which are typically associated with databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG).
